cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CE, cs.CR, cs.SI

This paper focuses on the impact of the repeal of net neutrality on communication networks, specifically in the context of video delivery. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses a techno-economic Mixed Integer Linear Programming (MILP) model to optimize the prices of different classes of service, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper considers the impact on network energy efficiency, which could fall under the category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.SI (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper also discusses the potential for discrimination against data-intensive content, which could fall under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
